title: EastEnders fans in uproar as soap is mysteriously SCRAPPED: 'Its becoming a joke!'
text:
EastEnders fans in uproar as soap is mysteriously SCRAPPED: 'Its becoming a joke!' EastEnders fans in uproar as soap is mysteriously SCRAPPED: 'Its becoming a joke!' EASTENDERS fans took to Twitter to vent their anger this evening after they realised their favourite soap wouldn't be on television tomorrow night. PUBLISHED: 21:39, Thu, Feb 2, 2017 | UPDATED: 21:44, Thu, Feb 2, 2017 
It's not the first time EastEnders has been scrapped in favour of another programme, but that didn't stop viewers voicing their frustration online. 
The BBC One soap won't be aired until Monday at 8pm, with Spy in the Wild being shown at 7.30pm in its place, before Room 101 at 8.30pm. 
One person posted: "@BBCOne EastEnders isn't on tomorrow, what's the reason? Football? No Spy in The World end of series! Bloody disgusting." 
"Why isn't EastEnders on tomorrow?" a second then asked. BBC EastEnders fans are furious that the soap isn't on tomorrow night BBC EastEnders will continue on Monday night Related articles
